### eBGP Behavior

__Drop BGP Route Advertisement from the same AS_PATH__

Normally, BGP drops any route containing its own AS to prevent loops.


`AS-Override`
Modifies the AS_PATH so that the AS number is replaced when advertising a route to the peer.
Modifies AS_PATH outbound


<br>


`AllowAS-in`
Ignore the default behavior of BGP and allow BGP routes with the same AS-PATH to be learned.


<br>


